libccd
------------------------------------------
libccd implements variation on Gilbert-Johnson-Keerthi (GJK) algorithm +
Expand Polytope Algorithm (EPA). It also implements Minkowski Portal
Refinement (MPR, a.k.a. XenoCollide) algorithm as published in Game
Programming Gems 7.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.9.0-3
  libccd-devel-2.0-1bl2
  libccd2-2.0-1bl2
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.28-3
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2
  python-2.7.13-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/danfis/libccd

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/danfis/libccd/archive/v2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libccd-2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libccd-2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libccd-2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libccd-2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libccd2-2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libccd-devel-2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libccd)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libccd.README
  /usr/share/doc/libccd/README

(libccd2)
  /usr/bin/cygccd-2.dll

(libccd-devel)
  /usr/include/ccd/ccd.h
  /usr/include/ccd/compiler.h
  /usr/include/ccd/config.h
  /usr/include/ccd/quat.h
  /usr/include/ccd/vec3.h
  /usr/lib/libccd.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/ccd.pc

------------------

